![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20026376/31528727-babbdbbc-b007-11e7-9181-bc24460ae92e.png)

It seems odd to me that before the number 100, the interval is 20, but after 100, the interval is 60. I wonder in which case you need this feature?

Here's a demo I made for you:
http://gallery.echartsjs.com/editor.html?c=xSJNEgnT2-&v=1

```
    xAxis:{
        interval: 10,
        min: 30,
        axisLabel: {
            formatter: function (v) {
                if (v > 30 && v % 20 === 0) {
                    return v;
                } 
            }
        },
        axisTick: {
            show: false
        },
        splitLine: {
            lineStyle: {
                color: ['transparent', '#aaa']
            }
        }
    },
```

